37.body:
An input goes through multiple methods in series. This treats an umbrella request using different specific methods, depending on the method does. Keywords: series Spring Boot: FilterChain An HTTP request is passed through a series of filters ("filter chain") before rreaching the destination controller. This is an example of the Chain of Responsibility pattern beacuase it allows the filterrs to be organised in a chain. Each filter has the ability to either handle the request or pass it along. A common idiom is chain.doFilter() Python content_filter = ContentFilter([offensive_filter, ads_filter, porno_video_filter])
filtered_content = content_filter.filter(content) class ContentFilter(object): def __init__(self, filters=None): self._filters = list() if filters is not None: self._filters += filters def filter(self, content): for filter in self._filters: content = filter(content) return content
